<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="196" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<number box="[151,164,1337,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1.0">1</number>
. Metasoma laterally yellow, with broad dorsal longitudinal black stripe extending entire length of metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[1262,1321,1337,1358]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,969,992]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,948]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,948]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Megarhyssa gratiosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ: 4 — head and mesosoma, left; 5 — head and mesosoma, dorsal; 6 — metasoma, left; 7 — metasoma, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218642/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
Fig. 
<number box="[1307,1321,1337,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Fore wing hyaline with conspicuous subapical dark mark at apex of the radial cell (
<figureCitation box="[915,973,1366,1387]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1608,1631]" captionTargetBox="[229,1363,1083,1558]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[229,1364,1072,1558]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 8. Megarhyssa gratiosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ: wings, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
Fig. 
<number box="[960,973,1366,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Flagellum of antenna blackish with broad subapical pale band (
<figureCitation box="[394,452,1397,1418]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1667,1690]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,267,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[308,1285,267,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Megarhyssa gratiosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ: 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — antenna, dorso-lateral; 3 — mid and hind legs, ventro-lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218641/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
Fig. 
<number box="[438,452,1397,1418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheath 
<number box="[646,676,1397,1418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="3.4">3.4</number>
<emphasis box="[676,691,1396,1419]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">×</emphasis>
as long as fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[903,958,1397,1418]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1667,1690]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,267,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[308,1285,267,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Megarhyssa gratiosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ: 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — antenna, dorso-lateral; 3 — mid and hind legs, ventro-lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218641/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
Fig. 
<number box="[948,958,1397,1418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
)....................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1237,1353,1397,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megarhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gratiosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1237,1353,1397,1418]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">M. gratiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1359,1435,1397,1418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1359,1435,1397,1418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
- Metasoma with variable amount of yellow, reddish orange and black; tergites often transversely banded or with dorsal and/or lateral marks, but never with continuous median black stripe extending along entire length of metasoma. Fore wing without apical dark mark, or with radial cell darkened only at base (
<bibRefCitation author="Townes" box="[788,1023,1486,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" refString="Townes, H. K. &amp; Townes, M. (1960) Ichneumon-flies of America north of Mexico: 2. Subfamilies Ephialtinae, Xoridinae, Acaenitinae. United States National Museum Bulletin, 216 (2), 1 - 676. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.216.1 - 2" type="journal article" year="1960">
Townes &amp; Townes 
<number box="[972,1023,1486,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 
<number box="[1076,1114,1486,1507]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="319.0">319</number>
, 
<emphasis box="[1123,1159,1486,1507]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">d–g</emphasis>
). Flagellum of antenna more or less entirely black, sometimes somewhat lighter in the apical half, never with contrasting pale band. Ovipositor sheath about 
<number box="[225,253,1547,1568]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1.9">1.9</number>
–3.0 
<emphasis box="[297,312,1545,1568]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">×</emphasis>
as long as fore wing........................................................................... 
<number box="[1424,1436,1547,1568]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2.0">2</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<number box="[151,165,1577,1598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2.0">2</number>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[225,273,1577,1598]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg with coxa and tarsus entirely black, femur and tibia black in basal 
<number box="[956,986,1577,1598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="0.8">0.8</number>
and yellow in apical 
<number box="[1194,1227,1577,1598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="0.2">0.2</number>
. Head and mesosoma black with yellow markings (
<bibRefCitation author="Kasparyan" box="[506,764,1606,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" refString="Kasparyan, D. R. (2002) A new species of Megarhyssa Ashmead, 1900 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) from Mexico. Russian Entomological Journal, 11 (3), 305 - 306." type="journal article" year="2002">
Kasparyan 
<number box="[616,668,1606,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2002.0">2002</number>
: 
<figureCitation box="[677,764,1606,1627]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1667,1690]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,267,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[308,1285,267,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Megarhyssa gratiosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ: 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — antenna, dorso-lateral; 3 — mid and hind legs, ventro-lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218641/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
). Metasoma extensively black, tergites 
<number box="[1145,1157,1606,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[1205,1217,1606,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2.0">2</number>
with pre-apical dorsomedian yellow marks, tergites 
<number box="[518,529,1637,1658]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="3.0">3</number>
+ with lateral yellow markings (
<bibRefCitation author="Kasparyan" box="[835,1089,1637,1658]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" refString="Kasparyan, D. R. (2002) A new species of Megarhyssa Ashmead, 1900 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) from Mexico. Russian Entomological Journal, 11 (3), 305 - 306." type="journal article" year="2002">
Kasparyan 
<number box="[945,997,1637,1658]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2002.0">2002</number>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1005,1089,1637,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1667,1690]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,267,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[308,1285,267,1643]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Megarhyssa gratiosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ: 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — antenna, dorso-lateral; 3 — mid and hind legs, ventro-lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218641/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
). Malar space 
<number box="[1229,1259,1637,1658]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1.4">1.4</number>
<emphasis box="[1259,1274,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">×</emphasis>
as long as apical width of mandible. Ovipositor sheath 
<number box="[588,618,1669,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1.9">1.9</number>
<emphasis box="[618,633,1668,1691]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">×</emphasis>
as long as fore wing. [Distribution: Central 
<collectingCountry box="[1057,1130,1669,1690]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(State of 
<collectingCountry box="[1224,1301,1669,1690]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Mexico</collectingCountry>
)]......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Kasparyan, 2002" authorityName="Kasparyan" authorityYear="2002" box="[1182,1436,1700,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megarhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae">
<emphasis box="[1182,1267,1700,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">M. verae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kasparyan" box="[1273,1436,1700,1721]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" refString="Kasparyan, D. R. (2002) A new species of Megarhyssa Ashmead, 1900 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) from Mexico. Russian Entomological Journal, 11 (3), 305 - 306." type="journal article" year="2002">
Kasparyan, 
<number box="[1388,1436,1700,1721]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
- 
<collectingCountry box="[225,273,1729,1750]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg predominantly brownish orange with yellow marks. Head and mesosoma predominantly yellow and brown. Metasoma yellow to reddish brown, with more or less distinct transverse pre-apical yellow bands on tergites. Malar space about 
<number box="[225,255,1789,1810]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="0.7">0.7</number>
<emphasis box="[255,270,1788,1811]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">×</emphasis>
as long as apical width of mandible. Ovipositor sheath about 3.0 
<emphasis box="[908,923,1788,1811]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">×</emphasis>
as long as fore wing. [Distribution: southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1370,1436,1789,1810]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">U.S.A.</collectingCountry>
from Texas to 
<collectingCountry box="[364,441,1820,1841]" name="Georgia" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Georgia</collectingCountry>
and Florida, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[655,728,1820,1841]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(Chihuahua).]................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1771" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" box="[1063,1436,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megarhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="macrura" subSpecies="macrura">
<emphasis box="[1063,1266,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">M. macrura macrura</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 
<number box="[1380,1429,1820,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" value="1771.0">1771</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
